description: Almost a billion voters took part in elections just held in India, and the campaign was marked by deepfakes generated by artificial intelligence across India's social media. The A.I.-generated content could be a sign of what's to come in the U.S. NBC News' Janis Mackey Frayer reports.
title: Election-related A.I. deepfakes spread across India's social media

description: In an interview with Time Magazine, President Biden said "there is every reason" for people to conclude that Israel's Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu is prolonging the conflict with Hamas for political reasons. The comment drew backlash from the Israeli government and President Biden later clarified his words. NBC News' Gabe Gutierrez reports.
title: New signs of tension between Biden and Israel's Netanyahu over war

description: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi will likely be elected to a third term, but opposition parties made bigger gains than expected after the country completed what has been called the largest election ever. NBC News’ Janis Mackey Frayer reports on the top issues facing India today including high unemployment among young people.
title: Modi close to third term as final votes tallied in a historically large Indian election

description: Footage released by Israel's fire and rescue agency showed a forest burning in northern Israel. The blaze is said to have been caused by rockets fired by the militant group Hezbollah in Lebanon.
title: Fires caused by Hezbollah rockets spread through northern Israel

description: India started counting votes from its six-week election that was seen as a referendum on Prime Minister Narendra Modi's decade in power. Nearly 970 million people, more than 10% of the world’s population, were eligible to vote and turnout averaged 66%, according to official data.
title: India awaits results in mega-election seen as referendum on Modi
